Metadata cache patterns:

              cache-aside:

                             cache does not interact with data store directly

                             not suitable if latency is critical

                                           can be mitigated by proper expiration value

                             prone to data cache stampede

                            

              read through cache

                             cache is responsible for reading data store in case of cache miss

                             like write through simplifies code

                                           may contain lots of rarely used entries

                                           whole system goes down if cache goes down

                             helps mitigate stampede problem

              write through cache

                             cache and data store write updated synchronously

              write behind pattern

                             cache writes to data store asynchronously

                             vulnerable to data loss if for e.g cache crashes

