              push vs pull

                             pull

                                           consumers pull message from a broker when they need a message

                                           optimized for throughput

                                                          can consume as much or little as you need

                                           better suited for message replay

                                                          very useful for debug for e,g

                                           worse latency

                                                          you query broker all the time

                             push

                                           broker pushes messages to consumers when the message arrives

                                           optimized for latency

                                                          no need to query the broker all the time

                                           client logic is simpler

                             load balancing is easy

                             flow control is difficult

                                           need to make sure consumers are not overwhelmed/starving

                             broker logic is more complicated

                            

                             no clear winner

                            

